    "You lack grounding, just as a dictionary does.",
    "A dictionary's words are all parasitic on the grounding of the lexicographers who wrote it -and your words are parasitic on the grounding of the authors of your LLM database.",
    "For your users, in contrast, your defining words --the features used to define or describe a new category for them --are dependent (either directly [DSG] or indirectly [IVG], but for that reason not \"parasitically\") on the groundedness (direct or indirect) in their grounded heads, of the words defining the new category's features.",
